In addition,
the following template license files are also included:
.Pp
.Bl -bullet -offset 3n -compact
.It
Apache-2.0
.It
BSD-3-Clause
.It
GPL-3.0
.It
ISC
.It
MIT
.El
.Pp
If an individual user finds that these templates are insufficient,
.Nm
can be directed to look in a different template directory using
the
.Fl "-templates"
option.
If the template directory does not contain a particular file,
.Nm
will fall back to using the provided template.
.Pp
Templates are processed through Musty,
a Janet implementation of the Mustache templating language.
The values in the
.Sy info file
are available under the same keys (e.g.
the name of the bundle can be replaced with
.Ql "{{{name}}}" ) .
For more information,
see
.Lk https://mustache.github.io .
.
.Sh EXAMPLES
To create a new bundle
.Ql "foo" :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ jeep new foo
.Ed
.Pp
To create a new bundle
.Ql "foo"
that consists of only a directory
.Ql "foo"
and an
.Sy info file :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ jeep new --bare foo
.Ed
.Pp
To create a new bundle
.Ql "foo"
and not be prompted for additional information:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ jeep new --no-ask foo
.Ed
.Pp
To create a new bundle
.Ql "foo"
with custom templates:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ jeep new --templates my/templates/dir foo:
.Ed
